<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-27T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="272" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/859</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Havre</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-27T21:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1917, 9 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 28, 7.35
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>93. <persName corresp="#p_DCC1">De Broqueville</persName> told me
                                this afternoon that the Belgian Government considers as insolence
                                the postscript to the German reply to the Pope and said that it adds
                                insult to injury.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_WB1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitlock</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>